message.content:
Implement "Your Money This Month" Widget

Skip the suggestion feature (e.g. "You have 3 streaming subscriptions…") for now — comment it out.


Backend
1. /financial/dashboard endpoint

Add a new field to the JSON response for this widget
The endpoint already accepts an optional month query param — pass it through to the DB query (default to current month if omitted), following the same pattern already used

2. Response shape
Design the structure to be dynamic — if a new type_category is added to the DB in future, it should appear in the response automatically without code changes, and render on the FE without changes too. Tweak the schema below if needed to support that:
json{
  "yourMoneyThisMonth": {
    "income": {
      "total": 0,
      "sections": [
        {
          "sectionKey": "income",
          "sectionLabel": "Income",
          "items": [
            { "description": "string", "amount": 0 }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "outgoing": {
      "total": 0,
      "sections": [
        {
          "sectionKey": "debtRepayment",
          "sectionLabel": "Debt Repayment",
          "items": [
            { "description": "string", "amount": 0 }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionKey": "essentialBills",
          "sectionLabel": "Essential Bills",
          "items": [
            { "description": "string", "amount": 0 }
          ]
        }
        // additional categories appear here dynamically
      ]
    }
  }
}
3. Database query / service function

Group financial records by type_category (e.g. "Income", "Essential Bills", "Debt Repayment", etc.)
Compute all fields required by the schema above
Scope strictly to the logged-in user — no other user's records should be returned


Frontend

Call the /financial/dashboard endpoint and render the "Your Money This Month" widget
Iterate over sections dynamically — don't hardcode category names


Backend Integration Tests
Cover all of the following:
ScenarioDetailCorrect groupingIncome records → income, all otgUser isolationOnly records belonging to the authenticated user are returnedField & calculation accuracyEvery field, every total, every section subtotalDynamic categoriesA new type_category appears in the response automaticallyEdge casesNo records, single category only, zero amounts, missing month param (defaults to current month), user with no transactions

